@using PQDashboard.Model
@model AppModel
<div class="alert alert-danger" role="alert">These system settings control application appearance and behavior - edit with care.</div>
<p>
    By clicking on the menu items to the left, the following system elements can be configured:
</p>
<ol>
    <li>
        The <b>System Pages</b>. This is the list of pages that are configured in the system. You can edit pages to control it's title, page location,
        server and client key/value pair configuration, as well as included and excluded roles that will control if a page is allowed to show up in a
        menu based on a user's defined roles.
        <em>Note that adding a new MVC based page will require a route be placed into the corresponding view controller.</em>
    </li>
    <li>
        The <b>System Menus</b>. This is the list of menus that are defined in the system. You can edit the menu details as well as control the
        menu items (i.e., the <em>system pages</em> or external links) that will appear in the menu. For each menu item you can edit the image,
        menu item text and the order of items for the menu.
    </li>
    <li>
        The <b>System Value Lists</b>. This is the list of enumerations and values defined for the system that most often appear in drop-downs through-out
        the system. You can edit the value list group details as well as control the list items that will appear in the group. For each value item you can
        edit the primary key value and various enumeration options for the list item as well as its sort order.
    </li>
</ol>
<p>
    Click on "Settings" to go back to the primary PQDashboard settings.
</p>
